	<entry>
		<title>yet another easy way to get root access, through telnetenabled</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="http://www.openstora.com/component/content/article/34-stora/51-yet-another-easy-way-to-get-root-access-through-telnetenabled"/>
		<published>2010-06-03T18:42:41Z</published>
		<updated>2010-06-03T18:42:41Z</updated>
		<id>http://www.openstora.com/component/content/article/34-stora/51-yet-another-easy-way-to-get-root-access-through-telnetenabled</id>
		<author>
			<name>pippone</name>
		<email>neothematrix@libero.it</email>
		</author>
		<summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;There's one more easy way to get root access to the Stora, this time by enabling the telnet daemon that is running by default on each device.&lt;br /&gt;How to do that:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Download the TelnetEnabler file/script, .exe version (&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.hardwarehackersunite.com/remository/Stora/Tools/TelnetEnable-for-Windows/&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;) if you have Windows or python script (&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.hardwarehackersunite.com/remository/Stora/Tools/TelnetEnable-for-all-platform-%28python-script%29/&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;) for all other platform (of course you can use the python script even on Windows, but that requires Python interpreter).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Get your Stora ip and mac address (the mac address can be obtained using &quot;arp -a&quot; or looking behind the Stora, there's a sticker with the MAC address printed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run the .exe or the python script with the following options:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;padding-left: 60px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For the Windows version:&lt;/strong&gt; telnetenable.exe STORA_IP STORA_MAC_ADDRESS Gearguy Geardog&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;padding-left: 60px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For the python version&lt;/strong&gt;: python telnetenable.py STORA_IP STORA_MAC_ADDRESS Gearguy Geardog&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you did all this correctly, telnet should be enabled on the stora allowing you to just &quot;telnet STORA_IP&quot; and get root access.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;From that point on, follow the tutorial on the wiki or on the forum to get the best from your Stora!&lt;/p&gt;</summary>
		<content type="html">&lt;p&gt;There's one more easy way to get root access to the Stora, this time by enabling the telnet daemon that is running by default on each device.&lt;br /&gt;How to do that:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Download the TelnetEnabler file/script, .exe version (&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.hardwarehackersunite.com/remository/Stora/Tools/TelnetEnable-for-Windows/&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;) if you have Windows or python script (&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.hardwarehackersunite.com/remository/Stora/Tools/TelnetEnable-for-all-platform-%28python-script%29/&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;) for all other platform (of course you can use the python script even on Windows, but that requires Python interpreter).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Get your Stora ip and mac address (the mac address can be obtained using &quot;arp -a&quot; or looking behind the Stora, there's a sticker with the MAC address printed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run the .exe or the python script with the following options:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;padding-left: 60px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For the Windows version:&lt;/strong&gt; telnetenable.exe STORA_IP STORA_MAC_ADDRESS Gearguy Geardog&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;padding-left: 60px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For the python version&lt;/strong&gt;: python telnetenable.py STORA_IP STORA_MAC_ADDRESS Gearguy Geardog&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you did all this correctly, telnet should be enabled on the stora allowing you to just &quot;telnet STORA_IP&quot; and get root access.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;From that point on, follow the tutorial on the wiki or on the forum to get the best from your Stora!&lt;/p&gt;</content>
